<para><anchor id="md__2tmp_2github__repos__arch__doc__gen_2yshishenya_2rob_2docs_2README_1autotoc_md177"/> This website is built using <ulink url="https://docusaurus.io/">Docusaurus 2</ulink>, a modern static website generator.</para>
<sect1 id="md__2tmp_2github__repos__arch__doc__gen_2yshishenya_2rob_2docs_2README_1autotoc_md178">
<title>Prerequisites</title><para>To build and test documentation locally, begin by downloading and installing <ulink url="https://nodejs.org/en/download/">Node.js</ulink>, and then installing <ulink url="https://classic.yarnpkg.com/en/">Yarn</ulink>. On Windows, you can install via the npm package manager (npm) which comes bundled with Node.js:</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".console"><codeline><highlight class="normal">npm<sp/>install<sp/>--global<sp/>yarn</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="md__2tmp_2github__repos__arch__doc__gen_2yshishenya_2rob_2docs_2README_1autotoc_md179">
<title>Installation</title><para><programlisting filename=".console"><codeline><highlight class="normal">pip<sp/>install<sp/>pydoc-markdown</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">cd<sp/>website</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">yarn<sp/>install</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="md__2tmp_2github__repos__arch__doc__gen_2yshishenya_2rob_2docs_2README_1autotoc_md180">
<title>Local Development</title><para>Navigate to the website folder and run:</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".console"><codeline><highlight class="normal">pydoc-markdown</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">yarn<sp/>start</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>This command starts a local development server and opens up a browser window. Most changes are reflected live without having to restart the server. </para>
</sect1>
